31/01/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government expects to finalise a deal with the United States on the joint use of military facilities by April, Defence Minister Veselin Bliznakov said in an interview published on Monday (30 January).
He said negotiations are at an advanced stage and the agreement could be signed during US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice's visit to Sofia in April, for a meeting of NATO foreign ministers.
(Reuters, Dnevnik - 30/01/06)
